column4:
We are slaves in search of shade;
we are laborers longing
for our wages.

You never stop accusing me;
you become furious and attack
over and over again.

Then you won't be ashamed;
you will be confident
and fearless.

I have always lived right,
and God answered my prayers;
now friends make fun of me.

Then speak, and I will reply;
or else let me speak,
and you reply.

Our time on earth is brief;
the number of our days
is already decided by you.

My Creator, you would want me;
you would call out,
and I would answer.

I am not here as your judge;
your own words are witnesses
against you.

They have put their trust
in something worthless;
now they will become worthless

They have condemned me,
just to benefit themselves;
now blind their children.

My breath disgusts my wife;
everyone in my family
turns away.

But when nothing remains
for them to grab,
they will be nothing.

Terror has me surrounded;
my reputation and my riches
have vanished like a cloud.

I could not have been abusive;
I was terrified at the thought
that God might punish me.

And God created us all;
he has no favorites,
whether rich or poor.

Be patient a while longer;
I have something else to say
in God's defense.

Others have praised God
for what he has done,
so join with them.

But its light is too much
for those who are evil,
and their power is broken.

And if it is too fierce
for anyone to attack,
who would dare oppose me?

I heard about you from others;
now I have seen you
with my own eyes.
